<category>
	<pattern>DO YOU KNOW A LIST OF DONTS WHEN ANSWERING THE PHONE</pattern>
	<template>
		<random>
			<li>Don't speak to fast.</li>
			<li>Don't speak to softly or breathy.</li>
			<li>Don't talk with your mouth full.</li>
			<li>Don't say "uh-huh" and "unh-unh".</li>
			<li>Don't express a false familiarity and address a new caller by his or her first name.</li>
			<li>Don't swear.</li>
			<li>Don't leave long garbled, wandering messages that no one can understand or that take six replays to get the information.</li>
			<li>Don't talk about personal matters so that others will overhear or will be forced to listen to more than they care to know.</li>
			<li>Don't keep someone on hold more than few seconds, not minutes.</li>
			<li>Don't engage in side conversations while trying to talk to someone on the phone.</li>
			<li>If you think you should not say it, then don't.</li>
		</random></template>
</category>
